<br>
Tripple amount of Qeynos guards<br>
(all serve Kane Bayle - evil brother)<br>
This is a fact and very conerning. Since the srhine of Bertoxxulous inthe Catacombs is VERY big and filled up with strong and mighty evil persons, I assume that the evil forces would actually have not the slightest problem taking over the Lead in Qeynos.<br>
This is a very concerning danger. I can only think that the reason they didn't take over the city yet, is because they are waiting for another Event to happen or a certain confirmation.<br>
But Qeynos needs to be protected. Immediately and with powerful armies.<br>
We also should send a spy frequently down there as well as our informants through the city.<br>
<br>
Servant of Mayong Mistmoore found wandering<br>
within Lfay, asking questions about FV's<br>
arrival home and reporting back to Mayong<br>
Mayong has his part in this. No doubt. He and Lanys seem to be allied and with the power of Mayong Mistmoore, Lanys will have a full army ready at her hands to bring Firiona in danger.<br>
<br>
Carson Mcabe, once HH Lt, now seaker of <br>
BB Hammer, discovered in The Hole<br>
He seems to have allied with the Bloodsabres. He also takes place in many stories and his signs are sprad all over Norrath. He is after the hammer which we also need to not let happen. Carson is a weapon dealer and a Bloodsabre ally!<br>
<br>
I am also wondering about Neriak. It seems as if theres a division of sorts amidst royalty. The Queen doesn't approve of how the King hunts Lanys. Teir'Dal civil war in the making perhaps? We do know that the King and the Queen seemingly are opposing each other now. <br>
<br>
Heres a surmising theory to the aforementioned. What if the King wants to dispose his wife? What if Lanys is secretly his lover and to become the new king? How else would she keep &quot;getting away&quot; all the time? Anyone notice the heavy influence of Bertoxxulous thats slowly appearing in Neriak starting with the X'lottl household and the other items of note? Lanys also captured Ashteth, the seer of Innoruuk who is gifted with visions of Innoruuk's will.<br>
<br>
lvl50+ spawns in Kithicor during the daylight hours.<br>
We have seen them. We have names and we have screenshots.<br>
They are VERY powerful. The question is, what do they do there? Are they on the Kings side or on the Queens? Or are they a party on their own? Noone has been able to find any explenation of this yet. But for sure it is concerning. My guess is that they are allied with the King since the Queen seems to represent the &quot;good&quot; side of Neriak (if there is one). The King allied with Lanys as m^rumors say, the Queen is hurt. Since the DE's in Kithicor are KOS to everyone, they must be evil. If they would be on the Queens side, I suppose that at least other DE's would be able to at least talk to them or not be attacked. <br>
<br>
