<br>
Bertoxxulous markings found near the<br>
X'lottl mansion (in Neriak).<br>
This goes in the same example as the treants rock signs. I suppose.<br>
<br>
Tayla Ironforge, which has a deep part in the story was originally a friend of Ton Firepride. Ton helped Tayla move, or more to the point introduced her to Carson who in fact did the move. Again note all the smugglers and Carson's dark elf contact to them outside the gates. Carson moved her to Neriak where she ended up in the maidens fancy where she was picked up by a &quot;powerful merchant&quot;.<br>
<br>
Here is our link. Mare X'lottl. SHE was in the Maidens Fancy where Tayla was. The inkeep THREW the game of Kings Court on purpose. Why? Think about what we know about House X'lottl. The &quot;powerfull merchant&quot; was none other then the Haggle Baron of Cabalis. Tayla Ironforge is STILL there now.<br>
<br>
<br>
The gnomes!<br>
The gnome with Edril's amulet IS in the Hole. He has actually and physically been seen. His name is Nortlav the Scalekeeper. There have been seen gnomes in the plane of hate, several! A gnome has been seen at the release of the Plague in the Lands of Karana. Also have been seen gnome messengers around.<br>
Those gnomes SEEM to not have allied with anyone and just be the good people. but this is WRONG!<br>
Those gnomes seem to in fact be part of this. They are in the background and hardly show up, but if they do, they certainly are involved in very important happenings.<br>
We must send a gnome spy in the City of Ak'Anon and have him find out more. Best would be a gnome necromancer.<br>
<br>
There are those half gods (ooc GMs) appearing and giving quests or giving small bits of information.<br>
So we have that Dark Elf appearing at the entrance of Befallen giving the following informations to a helper within the discussion:<br>
- The source of the Plague is &quot;some gods and I&quot;<br>
- being asked about an attack on Qeynos this eve  he answered &quot;Not this Eve&quot;. Saying this he still agreed that there WILL be an attak on Qeynos.<br>
- There is &quot;a lot more to Innoruuk in Plane of Hate than just the simple diety&quot;.<br>
-  and that &quot;Bertoxxulous is just a Servant of Innoruuk&quot;<br>
<br>
So this means 3 things.<br>
Qeynos WILL be attacked!<br>
We need to gather some forces and finally REALLY clear the plane of hate tosee what is going on there. This is also because (3rd thing we know) Bertoxxulous is a servant to Innoruuk. If this is so, then Innoruuk, again, is our true enemy. We need to find out more about this as much as (in this case) about the TIer'Dal and Dark Elfes in General. Neriak and Kithicor again take a more and more important position in this. We must keep Innoruuk and Neriak in mind, besides Qeynos and Bertoxxulous.<br>
<br>
The other GM event I heared of lately (thanks Brax) doesn't give new information but certainly CONFIRMS!<br>
